cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.MS, cs.ES

The paper proposes an artificial neural network that uses spintronic devices to mimic both neurons and synapses. This falls under the category of neuromorphic computing, which is typically classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of spintronic devices also involves the study of electromagnetics (cs.EM) and electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET). Additionally, the paper involves simulations and modeling (cs.MS) of the proposed network, and the use of nanoelectronics (cs.ES) for the implementation of the spintronic devices.
